@Node About "About"

                           @{b}About
                           =====@{ub}

@{b}Morphos@{ub}

This is quick port of the famous Sega Mega Drive/Genesis emulator for MorphOS.

Package contains three applications DGen, DGen-debugger and dgen2bin. Debugger
version is possibly unusable for normal gamers.

DGen has no GUI build in it. This MorphOS version has simple file requester to
help selecting ROMs and tool types to pass some most common command-line
arguments. DGen can also be used as command-line application.

I decided to port DGen because of lack of debugger in previous DGen port and
GenesisPlus.

- jvaltane


@{b}General@{ub}

DGen/SDL is a free, open source emulator for Sega Genesis/Mega Drive systems.
DGen was originally written by Dave, then ported to SDL by Joe Groff and
Phil K. Hornung in 1998.

Unfortunately, the project was abandoned at least since 2005 and much of its
history gone with its original home page.

In 2008, tamentis decided to try to relive DGen/SDL by registering this project
on SourceForge and made the source code of the last official release (version
1.23) available through CVS. He also created DGen's logo.

In August 2011, suddenly remembering Streets of Rage, I struggled to find a
Mega Drive (Genesis) emulator able to run it on my current setup
(Linux/x86_64), as most of them either targeted Windows, were completely
written in x86 assembly, or just didn't work for some reason.

Because DGen was my emulator of choice since 2002, I resolved to have a look at
the code and make it 64-bit-safe myself (only one month later, I found out that
some people on some forums already created patches for this purpose). After that
and some additional bugfixing, I noticed that tamentis was looking for a new
maintainer, so I offered my help along with a bunch of patches and got the
position.

DGen isn't the best Mega Drive/Genesis emulator out there, but it works and it's
probably the most portable. It's also perfect for command-line freaks.

- zamaz

@EndNode


@Node Features "Features"

              @{b}Features
              ========@{ub}

@{b}MorphOS@{ub}

 · Open file request if Dgen is launch from Ambient.
 · Added Tool types to some of the command-line options. Check @{"Tool Types" Link "ToolTypes"}
 · OpenGL works, but it is set off by default. Not all machines support it.
   · To enable OpenGL edit @{"Tool Types" Link "ToolTypes"} or @{"dgenrc" Link "Configuring"}
 · Doublebuffer disabled by default. Looks like some fullscreen modes do not work with doublebuffer.
   · To enable Doublebuffer edit @{"dgenrc" Link "Configuring"}
 · Saved user settings is set off default. Also known as dgenrc.auto
   · If you really need to enable saved user settings on, edit @{"dgenrc" Link "Configuring"}
 · Added MegaDrive2 and text/guide @{"icons" Links Icons}
 · Endianness fixes

@{b}General@{ub}

 · Game Genie/Hex codes support
 · PAL/NTSC, fullscreen modes
 · Joypad / joystick support
 · OpenGL textured video output
 · Portable (64-bit, endian safe), runs in Windows using MinGW
 · Screenshots, demos recording and playback
 · Musashi and StarScream (x86-only) CPU cores
 · CZ80 and MZ80 (generic and x86-only versions)
 · 16-bit, 8000 to 48000Hz sound output
 · Support for 8, 15, 16, 24 and 32 bpp modes
 · Archived/compressed ROMs support
   · MorphOS: works with lha, zip, bz2, gz and tar. Might require commands to path.
 · M68K debugger (contributed by Edd Barrett)
   · MorphOS: enabled in DGen-debugger. You have to run itfrom shell.
 · hqx and scale2x scaling filters

@EndNode


@Node Requirements "Requirements"
              @{b}Requirements
              ============@{ub}

 · MorphOS (>= 3.0)
 · PowerSDL
 · Optional: TinyGL

  Tested with PowerBook (MorphOS 3.1 & 3.2) and MacMini (MorphOS 3.1 & 3.2). PowerSDL v16.o.

@EndNode


@Node Installation "Installation"

              @{b}Installation
              ============@{ub}

Copy DGen directory where ever you like.

Dgen and Dgen-debugger. Recommented to leave where they are. These applications
create data directory to the PROGDIR:.

You can setup DGen with @{"tool types" Link "ToolTypes"} or @{"configure file" files Links "Configuring"}. First you should check
@{"Known problems" Link "Problems"} if you can or if you have to tweak some of features.

dgen2bin converts SMD-format Genesis/Mega Drive images to raw (BIN) format.
dgen2bin can be copied to C: if you like.

@EndNode


@Node ToolTypes "Tool Types"

                           @{b}Tool Types
                           ==========@{ub}
  GL
          Enable TinyGL/OpenGL. Fails to start if TinyGL/OpenGL is not available.

  FULLSCREEN
          Start as fullscreen if possible.

  PAL
          Emulate 50Hz PAL mode (as used in European models of the Mega Drive).

  RCFILE=<RCFILE>
          Load alternative rcfile.
  
  REGION=<E|J|U>
          Emulator region. Without this option, DGen uses the first
          region mentioned in the ROM header. It should be combined
          with -P for PAL mode. See below.

                 (none)             Autodetect (NTSC, 60Hz)
                 PAL                Autodetect (PAL, 50Hz)
                 REGION=J           Japan (NTSC, 60Hz)
                 REGION=J & PAL     Japan (PAL, 50Hz)
                 REGION=E           Europe (NTSC, 60Hz, music will certainly
                                    play too fast)
                 REGION=E & PAL     Europe (PAL, 50Hz)
                 REGION=U           America (NTSC, 60Hz)
                 REGION=U & PAL     Same as REGION=E & PAL

  XSCALE=<VALUE>
          Scale the window VALUE times in the X direction. VALUE must be a
          positive integer.
  
  YSCALE=<VALUE>
          Scale the window VALUE times in the X direction. VALUE must be a
          positive integer.
  
  SCALE=<VALUE>
          Scale the window VALUE times in both directions. Value must be a
          positive integer.
  
  SIZE=<WIDTHxHEIGHT>
          Desired window size (e.g. 640x480, 800x600, etc.)

  This part of the manual page was written by Joe Groff <joe@pknet.com>.
  Updated by zamaz <zamaz@users.sourceforge.net>
  ToolTypes version by Joni Valtanen (jvaltane at kapsi dot fi).

@EndNode

@Node CmdLine "Command-line"

                           @{b}Command-line
                           ============@{ub}

DGen [-Pfhmv] [-R (J|U|E)] [-H HZ] [-D DEMONAME] [-d DEMONAME] [-n USEC]
        [-p CODE,CODE...] [-r RCFILE] [-X XFACT] [-Y YFACT] [-S FACT]
        [-g (0|1)] [-G XxY] [-s SLOT] [romname [...]]

@{b}DESCRIPTION@{ub}

The ROM image in the file romname is executed, as emulated on a Sega Genesis or
Mega Drive running in 60Hz NTSC mode (unless the -P option is specified, in
which case 50Hz PAL mode is used).  romname should be in raw binary or SMD
format, and may be compressed with gzip(1), zip(1), or bzip2(1).

When romname isn't specified, DGen starts without a ROM. It can be loaded later
from the prompt. When more than a single romname is specified, they are
executed sequentially.

The options are as follows:

  -H HZ       Use a custom frame rate, can be used to accelerate or slow down emulation.
  -P          Emulate 50Hz PAL mode (as used in European models of the Mega Drive).
  -R (J|U|E)  Emulator region. Without this option, DGen uses the first region
              mentioned in the ROM header. It should be combined with -P for PAL mode. See below.
          (none)      Autodetect (NTSC, 60Hz)
           -P          Autodetect (PAL, 50Hz)
           -R J        Japan (NTSC, 60Hz)
           -R J -P     Japan (PAL, 50Hz)
           -R E        Europe (NTSC, 60Hz, music will certainly play too fast)
           -R E -P     Europe (PAL, 50Hz)
           -R U        America (NTSC, 60Hz)
           -R U -P     Same as -R E -P
  -f          Run fullscreen, if possible.
  -h          Show a brief synopsis of all options.
  -v          Show the version number, and exit.
  -D DEMONAME
              Play back a demo recorded with the -d option.
  -d DEMONAME
              Record a demo of the program running, which can be later replayed
              with the -D switch.
  -n USEC     Sleep for a number of microseconds after every frame, to give
              time to other processes.
  -p CODE,CODE...
              Modify the ROM image in memory, using Game Genie or Hex style
              codes. Game Genie codes are of the form ABCD-EFGH and Hex codes
              are in the form 123456:ABCD.  To specify more than one code,
              separate them with commas (do not use spaces).
  -r RCFILE   Parse another rc file after $HOME/.dgen/dgenrc. Values in the
              specified file override those in the preceding files.
  -X XFACT    Scale the window XFACT times in the X direction. XFACT must be a
              positive integer.
  -Y YFACT    Scale the window YFACT times in the Y direction. YFACT must be a
              positive integer.
  -S FACT     Scale the window FACT times in both directions. FACT must be a
              positive integer.
  -g (0|1)    Enable/disable OpenGL (if compiled-in).
  -G XxY      Desired window size (e.g. 640x480, 800x600, etc.)
  -s SLOT     Load the saved state from the given slot at startup (0-9)


  This part of the manual page was written by Joe Groff <joe@pknet.com>.
  Updated by zamaz <zamaz@users.sourceforge.net>
  AmigaGuide version by Joni Valtanen <jvaltane at kapsi dot fi>

@EndNode


@Node Prompt "Interactive prompt"

                       @{b}Interactive prompt
                       ==================@{ub}

  A minimalist interactive prompt inspired from vi(1) can be used to perform
  various operations described below. It is triggered by pressing colon (:), the
  default key. Command-line editing, history and completion are supported.

  @{b}Commands@{ub}
    {quit, exit, q}
          Quit, or load the next romname from command-line, if any.

    {load, open, plug, o} filename
          Load a given ROM filename.

    {unload, close, unplug}
          Unload the current ROM.

    reset
          Genesis reset.

    {ctv_push, ctv_pop, ctv_none}
          Manage the stack of Crap TV filters (if compiled-in).

    calibrate_js number
          Interactive calibration of the specified joystick.

  @{b}Variables@{ub}
    All configuration variables from dgenrc(5) can be displayed and modified
    interactively, with immediate effect.

    {int_name, bool_name, key_name, ...} {value}
          Affect value to variable name.

    {int_name, bool_name, key_name, ...}
          Display current value for variable name.


  ----------------
  This part of the manual page was written by Joe Groff <joe@pknet.com>.
  Updated by zamaz <zamaz@users.sourceforge.net>
  AmigaGuide version by Joni Valtanen <jvaltane at kapsi dot fi>

@EndNode


@Node Files "Files"

                           @{b}Files
                           =====@{ub}

  PROGDIR:data/dgenrc        Contains user settings for the emulator.
  PROGDIR:data/dgenrc.auto   Generated file containing saved user settings.
  PROGDIR:data/saves/*       Save states generated by the emulator.
  PROGDIR:data//ram/*        Battery-backup RAM images, generated by the
                             emulator for ROMs with save RAM.
  PROGDIR:data/screenshots/* Screenshots are generated there.
  PROGDIR:data/roms/*        ROMs default search path.
  PROGDIR:data/demos/*       Demos default search path.


  ----------------
  This part of the manual page was written by Joe Groff <joe@pknet.com>.
